      • canAttemptReconnect

        public boolean canAttemptReconnect()
        Gets if the client will be able to reconnect. This is false if, for instance, the client has been shutdown.
        Returns:
        true if the client can reconnect

      • willAttemptReconnect

        public boolean willAttemptReconnect()
        Gets if the client plans to reconnect to the server.
        Returns:
        true if the client will attempt to reconnect

      • setAttemptReconnect

        public void setAttemptReconnect(boolean reconnecting)
        Sets if the client will attempt to connect again. Note that this will only happen if canAttemptReconnect() is true as the client cannot try to reconnect if it has been shutdown. Setting to true will still result in a false willAttemptReconnect() if it is not able to reconnect.
        Parameters:
        reconnecting - true to reconnect, false to not reconnect

      • setReconnectionDelay
